extra.rawValue: "dev tun" will create a routed IP tunnel, "dev tap" will create an ethernet tunnel. Use "dev tap0" if you are ethernet bridging and have precreated a tap0 virtual interface and bridged it with your ethernet interface. If you want to control access policies over the VPN, you must create firewall rules for the the TUN/TAP interface. On non-Windows systems, you can give an explicit unit number, such as tun0. On Windows, use "dev-node" for this. On most systems, the VPN will not function unless you partially or fully disable the firewall for the TUN/TAP interface.
